to do for each anchor file

  • for the genes add column gene_exp with the TPM value of that gene (if available 0 else), these are split by "::"
  • for the TSS add column TSS_exp with the TPM value of that TSS (if available, 0 else), ""
  • for the motifs add column motif_exp with TPM values .. ""
  • for the motifs add column TF with TFs with TPM > 5
In [42]:
def get_exp(rna_df, sym, tissue,verbose=True):
    try:
        return rna_df.loc[sym,tissue]
    except KeyError:
        if verbose:
            print(sym, 'not found')
        return 0
In [43]:
def update_anchors(anchors_df,rna_tissue, thres=THRES, verbose=True):
    anchors_df['gene_exp'] = ''
    anchors_df['TSS_exp'] = ''
    anchors_df['motif_exp'] = ''
    anchors_df['TF'] = ''
    for idx, row in anchors_df.iterrows():
        if row['num_gene']>0:
            genes = row['gene'].split('::')
            genes_exp_arr = ['%.2f' % get_exp(rna_df, x.upper(), rna_tissue,verbose=verbose) for x in genes]
            anchors_df.at[idx, 'gene_exp'] = '::'.join(genes_exp_arr)
        if row['num_TSS']>0:
            TSSs = row['TSS'].split('::')
            TSS_exp_arr = ['%.2f' % get_exp(rna_df, x.upper(), rna_tissue,verbose=verbose) for x in TSSs]
            anchors_df.at[idx, 'TSS_exp'] = '::'.join(TSS_exp_arr)
        if row['num_motif']>0:
            motifs = row['motif'].split('::')
            motif_exp_arr = []
            TFs_arr = []
            for x in motifs:
                expr = get_exp(rna_df, x.upper(), rna_tissue,verbose=verbose)
                motif_exp_arr.append('%.2f' % expr)
                if expr>thres:
                    TFs_arr.append(x)
            anchors_df.at[idx, 'motif_exp'] = '::'.join(motif_exp_arr)
            anchors_df.at[idx, 'TF'] = '::'.join(TFs_arr)
    return anchors_df

In [47]:
for anchors_file in glob.glob(os.path.join(orig_bedpe_dir, "*merged.anchors.csv")):
    bed_file = '.'.join(os.path.basename(anchors_file).split('.')[:-1])+'.bed'
    new_file = os.path.join(new_bedpe_dir, bed_file)
    anchors_df = pd.read_csv(anchors_file, index_col=0, header=0)
    anchors_df['anchors'].str.split('_',expand=True).to_csv(new_file, sep='\t',header=False, index=False)

2B Merge files¶

1. Make bed files from anchor files
    a. From annotate_bedpe_csv_rna.ipynb
2. Sort bed files with bedtools sort
    a. `cd /Users/mguo123/Google Drive/1_khavari/omics_project-LD/diffloop_data/bedpe_files_csvs_rna`
    b. `for f in `ls *bed`; do echo $f; tissue=${f%%-*};echo $tissue; bedtools sort -i $f > ${tissue}_anchors_sort.bed; done`
    c. `cd /Users/mguo123/Google Drive/1_khavari/omics_project-LD/atac_footprinting/merged_into_anchors_hoco`
    d. `cp ../../diffloop_data/bedpe_files_csvs_rna/*sort.bed .`

3. Remove tab from end of footprinting files and then bedtools sort
    a. `cd /Users/mguo123/Google Drive/1_khavari/omics_project-LD/atac_footprinting/match_hoco`
    b. `#### sed 's/[[:blank:]]*$//'`
    c. `for f in `ls *bed`; do echo $f; tissue=${f%%_*};echo $tissue;f2=${tissue}_footprinting_hoco.bed; f3=${tissue}_footprinting_hoco_sort.bed; sed 's/[[:blank:]]*$//' $f > $f2; bedtools sort -i $f2 > $f3; done`
    d. `mv *footprinting_hoco_sort.bed ../merged_into_anchors_hoco`
4. Intersect tissue specific files
    a. `cd /Users/mguo123/Google Drive/1_khavari/omics_project-LD/atac_footprinting/merged_into_anchors_hoco`
    b. `mv Melanocytes_footprinting_hoco_sort.bed MC_footprinting_hoco_sort.bed`
    c. `mv GDS-D0_footprinting_hoco_sort.bed GDSD0_footprinting_hoco_sort.bed`
    d. `mv GDS-D3_footprinting_hoco_sort.bed GDSD3_footprinting_hoco_sort.bed`
    e. `mv GDS-D6_footprinting_hoco_sort.bed GDSD6_footprinting_hoco_sort.bed`
    f. `####bedtools intersect -wa -wb -a Air_anchors_sort.bed -b Airway_footprinting_sorted.bed -sorted -names footprinting -f 2.5E-6 > Airway_anchors_footprinting.bed`
    g. `for f in `ls *anchors_sort.bed`; do echo $f; tissue=${f%%_*}; echo $tissue; bfile=`find ${tissue}*footprinting_hoco_sort.bed`; echo $bfile; newfile=${tissue}_anchors_footprinting.bed; bedtools intersect -wa -wb -a $f -b $bfile -sorted -names footprinting -f 2.5E-6 > $newfile; done`

2C read in bedtools intersected files, merge into anchors file and update RNA¶

  • if rerunning anchors section, make sure to rerun section 4. based on

interesting aside 01/14/2020: seems to have a binning issue because the TSS of TP63 doesn't show up in any of the anchors for the tissues in which TP63 is expressed. it seems like the binning software called the loop anchors for this gene in the adjacent bin (downstream). it could be because the gene body is more open and more stuff can touch it thus the gene body has more "hits" for loops and the software calls the downstream 5kb bin rather than the region with the TSS

a work around is for each gene present in the gene column in anchor_df that doesn't have an annotated TSS within the anchor file, find the closest 5kb anchor and annotate as such

This is done in annotate_bedpe_csv_rna.ipynb 4th section

create tissue specific transcription factor footprinting tables¶

  • note: must only use human TFs because that would make the most sense for RNA seq comparison
  • footprints can overlap so the presence of a TF footprint means that the TF is expressed and something may be binding
  • two version, one version where the footprint needs to be in a tss and another version where it does not
  • TODO: is to do a correlation comparison to see which TFs overlap with which other TFs

In [59]:
# anchor specific
# read in hocomoco merged files, (takes about 7 minutes)
merged_anchor_hoco_files = glob.glob('atac_footprinting/merged_into_anchors_hoco/*anchors_footprinting.bed')
tissue_to_hoco = {}
for hoco_file in merged_anchor_hoco_files:
    tissue = os.path.basename(hoco_file).split('_')[0]
    # read in and process a bit
    hoco_df = pd.read_table(hoco_file, index_col=None, 
                            names=['anchor_chr', 'anchor_start', 'anchor_end', 
                                    'foot_chr', 'foot_start', 'foot_end', 'motif', 'score', 'strand'])
    hoco_df['anchors'] = hoco_df['anchor_chr'] + "_" + hoco_df['anchor_start'].map(str) + "_" + hoco_df['anchor_end'].map(str)
    hoco_df[['motif_abbr','motif_info']]=hoco_df['motif'].str.split("_",expand=True)
    hoco_df['motif_species'] = hoco_df['motif_info'].str.split('.',expand=True).loc[:,0]
    hoco_df['transcription_factor'] = hoco_df['motif_abbr'].map(hoco_motif_to_tf)
    hoco_df_filt = hoco_df[hoco_df['motif_species']=='HUMAN']
    # save this table
    new_file = os.path.join('atac_footprinting/merged_into_anchors_hoco/',tissue+'_anchors_footprinting.csv')
    hoco_df_filt.to_csv(new_file)
    # only keep the HUMAN motifs for future analyses
    tissue_to_hoco[tissue] = hoco_df_filt[['anchors', 'transcription_factor', 'foot_chr', 'foot_start', 'foot_end']]
    print(tissue, hoco_df_filt.shape)

In [62]:
# merge into anchors_file, takes about 5 minutes
new_anchors = {}
for anchors_file in glob.glob(os.path.join(orig_bedpe_dir, "*merged.anchors.csv")):
    tissue = os.path.basename(anchors_file).split('-')[0]
    print(tissue)
    anchors_df = pd.read_csv(anchors_file, index_col=0, header=0)
    # get appropriate motif information
    hoco_df = tissue_to_hoco[tissue]
    hoco_df_motifs = hoco_df.groupby('anchors').agg(
        {
            'transcription_factor':["count","nunique",lambda x: '::'.join(sorted(set(x)))]
        }
    )
    hoco_df_motifs.columns = ['num_motif_in_anchor','num_motif','motif' ]
    # drop JASPAR info and add HOCO info
    anchors_df.drop(['motif','num_motif'],axis=1,inplace=True)
    anchors_df = anchors_df.merge(hoco_df_motifs, how='left', left_on='anchors', right_index=True)

    # update rna
    rna_tissue = tissue_diffloop_to_rna[tissue]
    anchors_df_rna = update_anchors(anchors_df, rna_tissue, verbose=False)
    print(anchors_df.shape,anchors_df_rna.shape )
    # save new anchors_file
    new_file = os.path.join(new_bedpe_dir, os.path.basename(anchors_file))
    anchors_df_rna.to_csv(new_file)

In [205]:
def overlaps(a, b):
    """
    Return the amount of overlap, in bp
    between a and b.
    where a and b are tuples of size 2 consisting of [start,end] points, edges inclusive
    If >0, the number of bp of overlap
    If 0,  they are book-ended.
    If <0, the distance in bp between them
    """

    return min(a[1], b[1]) - max(a[0], b[0])

def percent_overlap(a,b):
    """
    returns the percentage of overlap between a and b
    a and b are tuples, (start,end)
    """
    max_overlap = min(a[1]-a[0],b[1]-b[0])
    return max(0,overlaps(a,b)/float(max_overlap))

In [230]:
#initialize storing 
# tf_tf_mat = np.zeros((len(tfs_list),len(tfs_list)))
tf_tf_dict = {}
for tf in tfs_list:
    tf_tf_dict[tf] = defaultdict(list)
    
# for each tissue, make sure tf_df is presorted by foot_end, foot_start, and foot_chr (already done)
# initialize list of tfs that overlap to `, and bool_overlap=False
# then walk through regions (only look in idx's  downstream to prevent double counting), if regions overlap add the TF to 
# after every region check for overlap, check to see if bool_overlap=False, if false, 
# Note: max TF length is 24 bps 
for tissue, tf_df in tissue_to_hoco.items():
    # INITIALIZE
    print(tissue, tf_df.shape)
    for foot_chr in tf_df.foot_chr.unique():
        tf_df_filt = tf_df[tf_df.foot_chr == foot_chr]
        tf_df_filt_list = list(zip(tf_df_filt['foot_start'], tf_df_filt['foot_end'], tf_df_filt['transcription_factor']))
        for idx, anchor in enumerate(tf_df_filt_list):
    #         # DEBUG
    #         if (idx %10000)==0:
    #             print(idx)

            s_start, s_end, s_tf = anchor[0], anchor[1], anchor[2]
            idx_check = idx+1
            while idx_check>0 and idx_check<len(tf_df_filt_list):
                t_start, t_end, t_tf = tf_df_filt_list[0][0], tf_df_filt_list[0][1], tf_df_filt_list[0][2]
                perc = percent_overlap((s_start, s_end),(t_start, t_end))
                if perc > 0:
                    tf_tf_dict[s_tf][t_tf].append(perc)
                    tf_tf_dict[t_tf][s_tf].append(perc)
                    idx_check+=1 #keep searching
                else:
                    idx_check=-1 # exit condition

        tf_tf_avg[s_tf][t_tf] = np.mean(tf_tf_dict[s_tf][t_tf])

4. annotating missing TSS¶

problem found in crms_tf_housekeeping

interesting aside: seems to have a binning issue because the TSS of TP63 doesn't show up in any of the anchors for the tissues in which TP63 is expressed. it seems like the binning software called the loop anchors for this gene in the adjacent bin (downstream). it could be because the gene body is more open and more stuff can touch it thus the gene body has more "hits" for loops and the software calls the downstream 5kb bin rather than the region with the TSS

a work around is for each gene present in the gene column in anchor_df that doesn't have an annotated TSS within the anchor file, find the closest 5kb anchor and annotate as such

This is done in annotate_bedpe_csv_rna.ipynb 4th section

  • note: then update anchors and save to same location as new_bedpe_dir 01/14/2020

for anchors_file in glob.glob(os.path.join(new_bedpe_dir, "*merged.anchors.csv")):
    start = time.time()
    tissue = os.path.basename(anchors_file).split('-')[0]
    anchors_df = pd.read_csv(anchors_file, index_col=0, header=0)
#     anchors_df['anchors'].str.split('_',expand=True).to_csv(new_file, sep='\t',header=False, index=False)
    
    gene_set = set()
    for gene_str in anchors_df.gene.unique():
        if type(gene_str)==str:
            gene_set=gene_set.union(set(gene_str.split('::')))

    TSS_set = set()
    for TSS_str in anchors_df.TSS.unique():
        if type(TSS_str)==str:
            TSS_set=TSS_set.union(set(TSS_str.split('::')))
            
    TSS_not_found = gene_set - TSS_set
    TSS_not_found = TSS_not_found.intersection(set(tss_df.gene))
    print(tissue, len(TSS_set), len(gene_set), len(TSS_not_found),time.time() - start)
    for tss in list(TSS_not_found):
        row = tss_df[tss_df.gene==tss].values[0]
        chrom_tss, loc_tss = row[0],row[1]
        anchors_df_filt = anchors_df[anchors_df.chr==chrom_tss]
        anchors_df_filt['how_close_start'] = abs(anchors_df_filt.loc[:,'start'] -  loc_tss)
        anchors_df_filt['how_close_end'] = abs(loc_tss - anchors_df_filt.loc[:,'end'])
        anchors_df_filt['how_close'] = anchors_df_filt.loc[:,['how_close_start','how_close_end']].min(axis=1)
        orig_row_idx = anchors_df_filt.sort_values('how_close').reset_index().loc[0,'index']
        orig_row = anchors_df.loc[orig_row_idx,:]
        if orig_row['num_TSS']==0:
            anchors_df.at[orig_row_idx,'num_TSS'] = 1
            anchors_df.at[orig_row_idx,'TSS'] = tss
        else:
            anchors_df.at[orig_row_idx,'num_TSS'] += 1
            anchors_df.at[orig_row_idx,'TSS'] += '::' + tss  
            
    
    print(tissue, 'done annotating TSSs...', time.time() - start)
    # update rna
    rna_tissue = tissue_diffloop_to_rna[tissue]
    anchors_df_rna = update_anchors(anchors_df, rna_tissue, verbose=False)
    anchors_df_rna.to_csv(anchors_file)
    print(tissue, 'done updating and saving...', time.time() - start)
